---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Header from '../components/Header.astro'
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro'

const toc = [
  { id: 'using', label: 'Using Union' },
  { id: 'accounts', label: 'Accounts' },
  { id: 'content', label: 'Your content' },
  { id: 'availability', label: 'Availability' },
  { id: 'privacy', label: 'Privacy' },
  { id: 'acceptable', label: 'Acceptable use' },
  { id: 'disclaimer', label: 'Disclaimer' },
  { id: 'liability', label: 'Limitation of liability' },
  { id: 'termination', label: 'Termination' },
  { id: 'billing', label: 'Subscription & billing' },
  { id: 'changes', label: 'Changes to these terms' },
  { id: 'contact', label: 'Contact' },
]
---

<Layout title="Terms" description="Union's terms of service.">
  <Header back />

  <section class="title-block">
    <div>
      <div class="eyebrow">Terms of service</div>
      <h1>Terms, <em>plainly.</em></h1>
    </div>
    <dl class="meta">
      <dt>Last updated</dt>
      <dd>July 2026</dd>
      <dt>Questions</dt>
      <dd><a href="mailto:support@unionwith.app">support@unionwith.app</a></dd>
    </dl>
  </section>

  <main class="doc">
    <aside class="toc" aria-label="Contents">
      <div class="lbl">Contents</div>
      <ol>
        {toc.map((t) => <li><a href={`#${t.id}`}>{t.label}</a></li>)}
      </ol>
    </aside>

    <article class="prose">
      <p class="welcome">Welcome to Union.</p>
      <p class="lede">
        These Terms of Service (“Terms”) govern your use of the Union app,
        website, and related services (“Services”). By using Union, you agree
        to these Terms. If you do not agree to these Terms, please do not use
        the Services.
      </p>

      <h2 id="using">
        <span class="h-num">§ 01</span>Using <em>Union</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        Union is designed to support reflection, prayer, journaling, and
        personal growth.
      </p>
      <p>
        You agree to use the Services lawfully and respectfully, and not to
        misuse, interfere with, or attempt to disrupt the platform.
      </p>
      <p>You must be at least 13 years old to use Union.</p>

      <h2 id="accounts">
        <span class="h-num">§ 02</span><em>Accounts</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        You are responsible for maintaining access to your account and for any
        activity that occurs under your account.
      </p>
      <p>
        We may suspend or terminate accounts that violate these Terms or misuse
        the Services.
      </p>

      <h2 id="content">
        <span class="h-num">§ 03</span>Your <em>content</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        You retain ownership of the content you create within Union, including
        journal entries, reflections, notes, and other personal content.
      </p>
      <p>
        By using the Services, you grant us permission to store and process
        your content solely for the purpose of operating and improving Union.
      </p>
      <p class="tagline">
        We do not claim ownership over your personal content.
      </p>

      <h2 id="availability">
        <span class="h-num">§ 04</span><em>Availability</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        We aim to keep Union available and reliable, but we cannot guarantee
        uninterrupted access at all times.
      </p>
      <p>
        Features may change, improve, or be removed over time as the product
        evolves.
      </p>

      <h2 id="privacy">
        <span class="h-num">§ 05</span><em>Privacy</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        Your use of Union is also governed by our <a
          class="inline"
          href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a
        >. Please review it to understand how we collect and use information.
      </p>

      <h2 id="acceptable">
        <span class="h-num">§ 06</span>Acceptable <em>use</em>
      </h2>
      <p>You agree not to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Use Union for unlawful purposes</li>
        <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to systems or accounts</li>
        <li>Interfere with the security or operation of the Services</li>
        <li>Upload harmful, abusive, or malicious content</li>
        <li>Reverse engineer or copy the Services without permission</li>
      </ul>

      <h2 id="disclaimer">
        <span class="h-num">§ 07</span><em>Disclaimer</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        Union is provided on an “as is” and “as available” basis. We make no
        guarantees regarding:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Continuous availability</li>
        <li>Accuracy of generated content</li>
        <li>Fitness for a particular purpose</li>
        <li>Uninterrupted or error-free operation</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="tagline">
        Union is intended for informational and personal use only and is not
        medical, mental health, legal, or professional advice.
      </p>

      <h2 id="liability">
        <span class="h-num">§ 08</span>Limitation of <em>liability</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        To the maximum extent permitted by law, Union and its operators will
        not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
        punitive damages arising from your use of the Services.
      </p>

      <h2 id="termination">
        <span class="h-num">§ 09</span><em>Termination</em>
      </h2>
      <p>You may stop using Union at any time.</p>
      <p>
        You may also delete your account at any time within the app by going to
        <code>Settings → Delete Account</code>.
      </p>
      <p>
        We reserve the right to suspend or terminate access to the Services if
        these Terms are violated.
      </p>

      <h2 id="billing">
        <span class="h-num">§ 10</span>Subscription &amp; <em>billing</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        Union may offer paid subscriptions that provide continued or full
        access to the Services. Any subscription is purchased and billed
        through your Apple App Store or Google Play account — not directly by
        us.
      </p>
      <p>
        A subscription may begin with a free trial. Unless you cancel before
        the trial ends, it automatically converts to a paid subscription.
        Subscriptions then renew automatically at the end of each billing
        period until you cancel.
      </p>
      <p>
        You can view, manage, or cancel a subscription at any time in your App
        Store or Google Play account settings. Deleting the app does not cancel
        a subscription. Cancellation takes effect at the end of the current
        billing period, and access continues until then.
      </p>
      <p>
        The price and billing period are shown at the point of purchase and may
        change over time, with notice where required. Payments are handled by
        the app stores; we do not receive or store your payment card details.
        Refunds, where available, are handled by the App Store or Google Play
        under their own policies.
      </p>

      <h2 id="changes">
        <span class="h-num">§ 11</span>Changes to these <em>terms</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        We may update these Terms from time to time. Continued use of the
        Services after changes become effective constitutes acceptance of the
        updated Terms.
      </p>

      <h2 id="contact">
        <span class="h-num">§ 12</span><em>Contact</em>
      </h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about these Terms, write to <a
          class="inline"
          href="mailto:support@unionwith.app">support@unionwith.app</a
        >.
      </p>

      <div class="ornament" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="line"></div>
        <span class="mark">&#10086;</span>
        <div class="line"></div>
      </div>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
